        </div>\n\n\n<p class="has-text-align-right has-small-font-size"><em>Outlaws of Thunder Junctino Key Art |
                Illustration by Lie Setiawan</em></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Yeehaw, Magic players! MTG’s been to Egypt, it’s been to
            ancient Greece, it’s supposedly going<em> to space</em> in the near future, but this year, we’re going where
            no
            planeswalker’s gone before: the western frontier. The 30<sup>th</sup> Anniversary panel revealed <em>Outlaws
                of
                Thunder Junction </em>as the Q2 <a href="https://draftsim.com/mtg-standard/">Standard</a> release of
            2024,
            and lemme tell you I’ve already got my pony saddled and my spurs at the ready!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Villains both
            iconic and new will come to a head on a brand-new plane dominated by baddies and inspired by western tropes,
            a
            setting fans have been clamoring for. Allow me to lasso y’all in: it’s time to dive into the rootinist,
            tootinist world that Magic’s ever visited!</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Outlaws of Thunder
