            </tbody>\n</table>\n<!-- #tablepress-271 from cache -->\n\n\n\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">About the
            Set: The Story</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure
            class="wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped wp-block-gallery-1 is-layout-flex wp-block-gallery-is-layout-flex">
            \n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="768" data-id="180313"
                    src="https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/vraska-concept-art-by-Kieran-Yanner-1024x768.jpg"
                    alt="Outlaws of Thunder Junction art by Kieran Yanner" class="wp-image-180313"
                    srcset="https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/vraska-concept-art-by-Kieran-Yanner-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/vraska-concept-art-by-Kieran-Yanner-300x225.jpg 300w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/vraska-concept-art-by-Kieran-Yanner-768x576.jpg 768w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/vraska-concept-art-by-Kieran-Yanner-1170x878.jpg 1170w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/vraska-concept-art-by-Kieran-Yanner-870x653.jpg 870w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/vraska-concept-art-by-Kieran-Yanner-390x293.jpg 390w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/vraska-concept-art-by-Kieran-Yanner.jpg 1200w"
                    sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p
            class="has-text-align-right has-small-font-size"><em><em>Outlaws of Thunder Junction Art | Illustration
                    by</em>
                Kieran Yanner</em></p>\n\n\n\n<p>There is quite a crossroads of characters on Thunder Junction, the
            Omenpath
            Arc blows in a couple surprises from familiar planes. The storyline follows the events of <em><a
                    href="https://draftsim.com/mtg-march-of-the-machine/">March of the Machine</a></em> and checks in
            characters from worlds that were invaded by the <a
                href="https://draftsim.com/mtg-phyrexian/">Phyrexians</a>.
            Omenpaths are essentially portals that allow individuals, not just planeswalkers, to travel between realms.
        </p>
        \n\n\n\n<p><em>Thunder Junction</em> notably takes place on a new <a
                href="https://draftsim.com/mtg-plane/">plane</a> that players haven’t visited before, so you feel far
            less
            of the aftermath of any interplanar invasion like with <em><a
                    href="https://draftsim.com/mtg-wilds-of-eldraine/">Wilds of Eldraine</a></em> or <em><a
                    href="https://draftsim.com/mtg-lost-caverns-of-ixalan/">The Lost Caverns of Ixalan</a></em>. You do
            get
            a heist, demons at work, and Kellan of Eldraine on the search for his father. Don't be a stranger to the
            Magic
            Story side of <em>Outlaws of Thunder Junction</em> and pull up <a
                href="https://magic.wizards.com/en/news/magic-story/episode-1-an-offer-of-revenge" target="_blank"
                rel="noreferrer noopener">Episode 1: An Offer of Revenge</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">
            Set
            Mechanics</h2>\n\n\n\n<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Commit a Crime</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure
            class="wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped wp-block-gallery-2 is-layout-flex wp-block-gallery-is-layout-flex">
            \n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async"
                    src="https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Forsaken-Miner_0088_EN.png" alt="" /></figure>
            \n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="733" height="1024"
                    data-id="183379"
                    src="https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Duelist-of-the-Mind-733x1024.png" alt=""
                    class="wp-image-183379"
                    srcset="https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Duelist-of-the-Mind-733x1024.png 733w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Duelist-of-the-Mind-215x300.png 215w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Duelist-of-the-Mind-390x545.png 390w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Duelist-of-the-Mind-300x419.png 300w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Duelist-of-the-Mind.png 744w"
                    sizes="(max-width: 733px) 100vw, 733px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure
                class="wp-block-image size-large">
                <img decoding="async" width="734" height="1024" data-id="184644"
                    src="https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/otj-108-tinybones-joins-up-734x1024.png" alt=""
                    class="wp-image-184644"
                    srcset="https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/otj-108-tinybones-joins-up-734x1024.png 734w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/otj-108-tinybones-joins-up-215x300.png 215w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/otj-108-tinybones-joins-up-390x544.png 390w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/otj-108-tinybones-joins-up-300x419.png 300w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/otj-108-tinybones-joins-up.png 745w"
                    sizes="(max-width: 734px) 100vw, 734px" />
            </figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You “commit a crime” when you
            <a href="https://draftsim.com/target-mtg/">target</a> an opponent, their permanent, spell, or a card in
            their
            graveyard. You care about targeting your opponent's things, so cards like <a class="tcg" rel="nofollow"
                target="_blank"
                href="https://tcgplayer.pxf.io/c/2226219/1830156/21018?subId1=card_hover_article&partnerpropertyid=1989897&u=https%3A%2F%2Ftcgplayer.com%2Fsearch%2Fmagic%2Fproduct%3Fq=Tinybones%20Joins%20Up">Tinybones
                Joins Up</a> that offers multiple targets from one spell are super effective. Keep your eyes peeled for
            the
            <a href="https://draftsim.com/best-activated-abilities-mtg/">great activated abilities</a> that target any
            creature.
        </p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Mounts and Saddle</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure
            class="wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped wp-block-gallery-3 is-layout-flex wp-block-gallery-is-layout-flex">
