                    sizes="(max-width: 733px) 100vw, 733px" />
            </figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Saddle up your horses and get a
            benefit if you &#8220;<a href="https://draftsim.com/mtg-vehicles-and-crew/">crew</a>&#8221; a mount which is
            a
            new <a href="https://draftsim.com/mtg-creature-types/">creature type</a>. The connection between saddle and
            mount figures to stay separate like <a href="https://draftsim.com/mtg-wall/">walls</a> and <a
                href="https://draftsim.com/mtg-defender/">defender</a>. One doesn't always appear with the other and can
            be
            altered without affecting the other.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not surprising that saddling The Gitrog ends badly for
            the
            creature on <a class="tcg" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"
                href="https://tcgplayer.pxf.io/c/2226219/1830156/21018?subId1=card_hover_article&partnerpropertyid=1989897&u=https%3A%2F%2Ftcgplayer.com%2Fsearch%2Fmagic%2Fproduct%3Fq=The%20Gitrog%2C%20Ravenous%20Ride">The
                Gitrog, Ravenous Ride</a>. I'm getting thirsty just thinking about sacrificing a creature with 2+ power.
        </p>
        \n\n\n\n<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Plot</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure
            class="wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped wp-block-gallery-4 is-layout-flex wp-block-gallery-is-layout-flex">
