                    sizes="(max-width: 733px) 100vw, 733px" />
            </figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The villain side of <a href="https://draftsim.com/party-mtg/">the party
                mechanic</a>, an outlaw is a permanent that is either: <a
                href="https://draftsim.com/mtg-assassin/">Assassin</a>, Mercenary, <a
                href="https://draftsim.com/mtg-pirate/">Pirate</a>, <a href="https://draftsim.com/mtg-rogue/">Rogue</a>,
            or
            <a href="https://draftsim.com/mtg-warlock/">Warlock</a>. You want to look closely at the subtypes like you
            did
            in <em><a href="https://draftsim.com/zendikar-rising/">Zendikar Rising</a></em>. Wizards also gives us this
            example, an ability may trigger whenever you cast an outlaw spell or return an outlaw creature card from
            your
            graveyard to the battlefield.
        </p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Spree</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure
            class="wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped wp-block-gallery-6 is-layout-flex wp-block-gallery-is-layout-flex">
            \n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="733" height="1024" data-id="184589"
                    src="https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Final-Showdown-733x1024.png" alt=""
                    class="wp-image-184589"
                    srcset="https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Final-Showdown-733x1024.png 733w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Final-Showdown-215x300.png 215w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Final-Showdown-390x545.png 390w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Final-Showdown-300x419.png 300w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Final-Showdown.png 744w"
                    sizes="(max-width: 733px) 100vw, 733px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure
                class="wp-block-image size-large">
                <img decoding="async"
                    src="https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dance-of-the-Tumbleweeds_0160_EN.png" alt="" />
            </figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="734" height="1024"
                    data-id="184591"
                    src="https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/otj-125-great-train-heist-734x1024.png" alt=""
                    class="wp-image-184591"
                    srcset="https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/otj-125-great-train-heist-734x1024.png 734w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/otj-125-great-train-heist-215x300.png 215w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/otj-125-great-train-heist-390x544.png 390w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/otj-125-great-train-heist-300x419.png 300w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/otj-125-great-train-heist.png 745w"
                    sizes="(max-width: 734px) 100vw, 734px" /></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This take on a modal spell
            includes additional costs for each effect. If you're able to cast it without paying its cost, you can think
            of
            it as a discount toward paying for the actual effect(s) you choose. The mana value of spree spells remains
            consistent, regardless of how much math you need to cast it.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">
            Speculation
        </h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="768"
                src="https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/human-with-ballistic-crossbow-art-by-Matt-Zeilinger-1024x768.jpg"
                alt="" class="wp-image-183353"
                srcset="https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/human-with-ballistic-crossbow-art-by-Matt-Zeilinger-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/human-with-ballistic-crossbow-art-by-Matt-Zeilinger-300x225.jpg 300w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/human-with-ballistic-crossbow-art-by-Matt-Zeilinger-768x576.jpg 768w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/human-with-ballistic-crossbow-art-by-Matt-Zeilinger-1170x878.jpg 1170w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/human-with-ballistic-crossbow-art-by-Matt-Zeilinger-870x653.jpg 870w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/human-with-ballistic-crossbow-art-by-Matt-Zeilinger-390x293.jpg 390w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/human-with-ballistic-crossbow-art-by-Matt-Zeilinger.jpg 1200w"
                sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p
            class="has-text-align-right has-small-font-size"><em>Outlaws of Thunder Junction Art | Illustration by Matt
                Zeilinger</em></p>\n\n\n\n<p>There’s little to go off at the moment, but the “Wild West” as a setting
            has
            been explored enough to get a sense of what we might expect to see. Think Red Dead <em>Redemption</em> but
            with
            mana instead of guns. For what it’s worth, it’s unclear whether <em>Thunder Junction</em> is an entire world
            or
            part of a larger plane.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here's the teaser from Magic's Head Designer Mark Rosewater on what to
            expect:</p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class="wp-block-quote">\n<p>• A new batch of five related creature types</p>
            \n\n\n\n<p>• A card capable of returning three different card types from the graveyard to the battlefield
            </p>
            \n\n\n\n<p>• A mechanic players have been asking us to do for many years gets made as the setting was the
                perfect place to finally do it</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• Dual lands with a land subtype that has never been on
                dual
                lands before</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• A new modal mechanic that introduces something different to think about</p>
            \n\n\n\n<p>• A card that can swap/exchange control of up to three different card types</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• A new
                creature token that has an ability no creature token has ever had before</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• A typal card
                for
                Skeletons and Zombies</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• Creature tokens in the set: (some might have abilities) 1/1 white
                Sheep, 1/1 blue Bird, 1/1 black Vampire Rogue, 1/1 red Mercenary, 2/1 green Varmint, 2/2 white Ox, 2/2
                white
                Spirit, 2/2 blue and black Zombie, 3/1 red Dinosaur, 3/3 white Angel, 3/3 green Elk, 4/4 red Scorpion
                Dragon, X/X green Elemental, */* Blue Ox</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• Some of the planes with legendary Villains in
                this
                set: Dominaria, Eldraine, Fiora, Innistrad, Ixalan, Kaladesh, Kaldheim, Kamigawa, New Capenna, and
                Ravnica
            </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, here are some rules text that will be showing up on cards:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• “Then
                repeat this process X more times.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• “if it wasn’t cast or no mana was spent to cast it.”
            </p>
            \n\n\n\n<p>• “Plotting cards from your hand costs <i class="mana-2"></i> less.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• “You can’t
                cast
                this spell during your first, second, or third turns of the game.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• “That card gains
                flashback <i class="mana-0"></i>”</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• “Target creature becomes a white Rabbit with a base
                power
                and toughness 0/1.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• “When you win that flip, copy that spell.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• “If a
                triggered ability of a legendary creature you control triggers, that ability triggers an additional
                time.”
            </p>\n\n\n\n<p>• “you get that many additional upkeep steps after this phase.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• “Oxen you
                control
                have double strike.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are some creature type lines from the set:</p>\n\n\n\n<p>•
                Creature
                – Armadillo</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• Creature – Shark Rogue</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• Creature – Plant Bard</p>\n\n\n\n<p>•
                Creature – Coyote</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• Creature – Homarid Mercenary</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• Creature – Rhino Brawler
            </p>
            \n\n\n\n<p>• Creature – Ox Angel</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• Creature – Porcupine Mount</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• Legendary
                Creature –
                Kor Advisor</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• Legendary Creature – Giant Scout</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Finally, here are some names
                in
                the set:</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• Claim Jumper</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• Form a Posse</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• Gold Rush</p>\n\n\n\n
            <p>•
                Great Train Heist</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• High Noon</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• Quick Draw</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• Reach for the Sky
            </p>
            \n\n\n\n<p>• Resilient Roadrunner</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• Shoot the Sheriff</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• This Town Ain’t Big
                Enough
            </p>\n
        </blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p>Magic has long avoided the depiction of actual guns in card art, though I’m
            pretty
            sure <a class="tcg" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"
                data-thumb="https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/mtg-card-DB/cards/5/7/570f7c90-109b-4d6d-8205-d158753719e8.jpg"
                href="https://tcgplayer.pxf.io/c/2226219/1830156/21018?subId1=card_hover_article&partnerpropertyid=1989897&u=https%3A%2F%2Ftcgplayer.com%2Fsearch%2Fmagic%2Fproduct%3Fq=Freelance%20Muscle">Freelance
                Muscle</a> is packing heat. However, at the very least, guns are a recurring feature of Western cinema,
            what
            with all of the standoffs, duels, and shoot-outs that take place. I hope actual guns will be minimal in the
            set,
            but there’s bound to be an equivalent. An early piece of art depicts a new character wielding what appears
            to be
            a firearm-adjacent weapon, possibly one that shoots projectiles. You know, nothing like an actual gun.</p>
        \n\n\n
        <div class="wp-block-image">\n<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img decoding="async" width="542"
                    height="306"
                    src="https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Key-Image-1-Illustration-by-Kieran-Yanner.jpg"
                    alt="Outlaws of Thunder Junction Art - Illustration by Kieran Yanner" class="wp-image-159562"
                    srcset="https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Key-Image-1-Illustration-by-Kieran-Yanner.jpg 542w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Key-Image-1-Illustration-by-Kieran-Yanner-300x170.jpg 300w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Key-Image-1-Illustration-by-Kieran-Yanner-390x220.jpg 390w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Key-Image-1-Illustration-by-Kieran-Yanner-480x270.jpg 480w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Key-Image-1-Illustration-by-Kieran-Yanner-133x75.jpg 133w"
                    sizes="(max-width: 542px) 100vw, 542px" /></figure>
        </div>\n\n\n<p>If we get some sort of ballistic equipment, I wonder if we’ll get an entire mechanic focused on
            duels. Mano-a-mano standoffs, if you will. Maybe the return of the <a
                href="https://draftsim.com/mtg-clash/">clash</a> mechanic? Or a fancy take on the <a
                href="https://draftsim.com/fight-mtg/">fight</a> mechanic? Whatever it is, someone’s shooting someone
            else
            with something.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s talk about the characters for a moment. The <a
                href="https://draftsim.com/mtg-planeswalkers/">planeswalkers</a> featured in each main set are very
            limited
            moving forward. And with much of the planeswalker roster being desparked in Aftermath, we’re still not sure
            exactly who’s able to planeswalk or not. Ral is on Thunder Junction, but not necessarily as a planeswalker.
            Jace
            has been reawakened and joins Oko as major plot players. But that brings us to our biggest early art piece
            for
            the set.</p>\n\n\n<div class="wp-block-image">\n<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img decoding="async"
                    width="640" height="359"
                    src="https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Key-Image-2-Lie-Setiawan.webp"
                    alt="Outlaws of Thunder Junctino Key Art - Illustration by Lie Setiawan" class="wp-image-159560"
                    srcset="https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Key-Image-2-Lie-Setiawan.webp 640w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Key-Image-2-Lie-Setiawan-300x168.webp 300w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Key-Image-2-Lie-Setiawan-390x220.webp 390w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Key-Image-2-Lie-Setiawan-480x270.webp 480w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Key-Image-2-Lie-Setiawan-133x75.webp 133w"
                    sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></figure>
        </div>\n\n\n<p>The headliner for <em>Thunder Junction</em> shows a ragtag group of silhouetted characters, most
            of
            which are immediately recognizable. We very clearly see Rakdos and Vraska in the group, Oko’s prominently
            featured in the art, and players were spot on, calling the character on the far left <a
                href="https://draftsim.com/tinybones-edh-deck/">Tinybones</a>, a skeletal Dominarian that hasn’t been
            prominently featured in a story yet. The character between Rakdos and Oko appears to be our new friend from
            the
            first art-piece, evident by the hat and weapon, which is definitely <em>not </em>a gun.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That
            leaves mysterious figure #3, which there doesn’t seem to be a consensus on. Some were correct in that Jace
            joins
            the set, given his story significance with Vraska, though it could also be <a class="tcg" rel="nofollow"
                target="_blank"
                data-thumb="https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/mtg-card-DB/cards/6/2/625b8023-2ef1-4b7b-9e48-4f774fee14e0.jpg"
                href="https://tcgplayer.pxf.io/c/2226219/1830156/21018?subId1=card_hover_article&partnerpropertyid=1989897&u=https%3A%2F%2Ftcgplayer.com%2Fsearch%2Fmagic%2Fproduct%3Fq=Old%20Rutstein">Old
                Rutstein</a> in different attire since he’s been revealed as a traveling caravanner of sorts in another
            piece of art.</p>\n\n\n<div class="wp-block-image">\n<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img
                    decoding="async" width="542" height="306"
                    src="https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Key-Image-3-Illustration-by-Javier-Charro.jpg"
                    alt="Oulaws of Thunder Junction Art - Illustration by Javier Charro" class="wp-image-159561"
                    srcset="https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Key-Image-3-Illustration-by-Javier-Charro.jpg 542w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Key-Image-3-Illustration-by-Javier-Charro-300x170.jpg 300w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Key-Image-3-Illustration-by-Javier-Charro-390x220.jpg 390w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Key-Image-3-Illustration-by-Javier-Charro-480x270.jpg 480w, https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Key-Image-3-Illustration-by-Javier-Charro-133x75.jpg 133w"
                    sizes="(max-width: 542px) 100vw, 542px" /></figure>
        </div>\n\n\n<p>The world of <em>Thunder Junction</em> is marketed as a place where villains congregate to find
            fortune and fame. Sounds great for the locals. This means you might see Magic equivalents of all the cliché
            tropes, like bank heists, bounties, and almost certainly <a
                href="https://draftsim.com/mtg-treasure/">treasure</a> tokens. Always with the <a class="tcg"
                rel="nofollow" target="_blank"
                data-thumb="https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/mtg-card-DB/cards/6/3/630c0d1c-9ddb-4e76-a82a-9cdd8a5b487b.jpg"
                href="https://tcgplayer.pxf.io/c/2226219/1830156/21018?subId1=card_hover_article&partnerpropertyid=1989897&u=https%3A%2F%2Ftcgplayer.com%2Fsearch%2Fmagic%2Fproduct%3Fq=Treasure">Treasure</a>
            tokens. Maybe we’ll even get a mean legendary sheriff to bring these villains to justice. Though I’d say,
            the <a href="https://draftsim.com/mtg-banned-list/">ban lists</a> are already doing a pretty good job of
            keeping
            Oko in ‘cuffs.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are a couple of bounty counter cards that seem to fit the villain bill:
        </p>
        \n\n\n\n\t<div class="card_gallery_wrapper">\n\t\t<a class="mtg-card-db-card single-card"
                href="https://tcgplayer.pxf.io/c/2226219/1830156/21018?subId1=card_img&partnerpropertyid=1989897&u=https%3A%2F%2Ftcgplayer.com%2Fsearch%2Fmagic%2Fproduct%3Fq=Bounty%20Hunter"
                rel="nofollow" target="_blank">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img width="265" height="370"
                    style="margin-bottom: 4px; border-radius:10px;" talt="Bounty Hunter"
                    src="https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/mtg-card-DB/cards/9/8/98319fd3-0aad-4fc3-bb83-3c027d0ed652.jpg" /></a><a
                class="mtg-card-db-card single-card"
                href="https://tcgplayer.pxf.io/c/2226219/1830156/21018?subId1=card_img&partnerpropertyid=1989897&u=https%3A%2F%2Ftcgplayer.com%2Fsearch%2Fmagic%2Fproduct%3Fq=Chevill%2C%20Bane%20of%20Monsters"
                rel="nofollow" target="_blank">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img width="265" height="370"
                    style="margin-bottom: 4px; border-radius:10px;" talt="Chevill, Bane of Monsters"
                    src="https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/mtg-card-DB/cards/f/e/fecbf0a3-ebe1-43b6-a720-462ba19002eb.jpg" /></a><a
                class="mtg-card-db-card single-card"
                href="https://tcgplayer.pxf.io/c/2226219/1830156/21018?subId1=card_img&partnerpropertyid=1989897&u=https%3A%2F%2Ftcgplayer.com%2Fsearch%2Fmagic%2Fproduct%3Fq=Termination%20Facilitator"
                rel="nofollow" target="_blank">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img width="265" height="370"
                    style="margin-bottom: 4px; border-radius:10px;" talt="Termination Facilitator"
                    src="https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/mtg-card-DB/cards/5/d/5db59164-f0b1-4b5a-b821-ad0b2e1612d1.jpg" /></a>\n\t
        </div>\n\n\n\n<p>Trains are central to many Westerns and a <a
                href="https://draftsim.com/mtg-vehicles-and-crew/">vehicle</a> that hasn't had much representation. The
            trains I'm thinking of carry people, treasure, and are something the characters have little control over,
            perhaps depicted as crew creatures that stay tapped to keep the vehicle online. Wouldn't a new <a
                class="tcg" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"
                data-thumb="https://draftsim.com/wp-content/uploads/mtg-card-DB/cards/8/7/87068116-6000-44ee-b47f-f5cb8c233bb2.jpg"
                href="https://tcgplayer.pxf.io/c/2226219/1830156/21018?subId1=card_hover_article&partnerpropertyid=1989897&u=https%3A%2F%2Ftcgplayer.com%2Fsearch%2Fmagic%2Fproduct%3Fq=Black%20Carriage">Black
                Carriage</a> make sense?</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Land</em>, ask a cinema student and they should agree that
            the
            land in a western is practically a character itself. The <a
                href="https://draftsim.com/mtg-land-types/">types of
                land</a> could be huge rock formations that loom over the strongest of heroes, or vast expanses of
            desert
            that separate people from help and danger.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>My personal wish list includes a few things: I’ll
            get
            to see more <a href="https://draftsim.com/mtg-desert/">Desert theme</a> like from <em><a
                    href="https://draftsim.com/mtg-amonkhet/">Amonkhet</a></em> and <em><a
                    href="https://draftsim.com/hour-of-devastation-mtg/">Hour of Devastation</a></em> revisited. I want
            a
            cactus in the art of <em>at least</em> 10 different cards. And most importantly, above all else, I want a
            card
            that makes Tumbleweed tokens. I don’t know what those would do, but I know I want them.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2
